Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tanisha C. Moses in court.  Attorney Anthony N Flitcroft in court for Tanisha C. Moses.  Prosecuting attorney Samuel Thomas Berg in court for the State of Wisconsin. Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
Adjourned initial appearance on September 20, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Tanisha C. Moses appeared by video, in custody.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by ADA Samuel Berg. Atty. Obi Uzowulu appears specially. Called. Appearances made.  Record by the Court as to charges and penalties.  Record by Atty. Uzowulu that the defendant is eligible for attorney, but one has not yet been appointed. Matter is assigned to Judge Drettwan, and court sets on her calendar for appointment of counsel. Court in recess.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for August 30, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Signed bond filed with the court.
See signature bond for conditions. Amended down to $1500 on 9/20/2022.

*AMENDED 9/20/2022: BOND AMENDED DOWN TO $1500 CASH
DEFENDANT MUST POST $2500 CASH

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol. Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any co-actor(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  CO-ACTOR(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH CO-ACTOR DARNELL WALKER. Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.
